div.p: The poll_wait() calls MUST occur before checking buffer_used.

ol.li: Concurrent Writer fills buffer and calls wake_up_interruptible().
wake_up finds NO ONE on the queue (registration hasn't happened).
Driver then calls poll_wait() to register.
Driver returns mask with no POLLIN.
VFS sleeps FOREVER even though data is waiting.

ul.li:
Driver:
Registers the wait queue via poll_wait.
Returns the current readiness mask.
Never sleeps inside .poll.

VFS:
Manages the timeout timer.
Manages the actual schedule() call.
Loops over all FDs until one returns a non-zero mask.

div.p: Memory alignment and cache line residency
Cache Line 1 (0x00-0x3F): cdev internal Cache Line 2 (0x40-0x7F): cdev end + mutex lock start Cache Line 3 (0x80-0xBF): read_queue + buffer pointer Cache Line 4 (0xC0-0xFF): used + open_count
